org.cloudgraph.hbase.graph

Class ExternalEdgeRecognizerRelationalBinaryExpr

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudgraph.query.expr.DefaultExpr
      • org.cloudgraph.query.expr.DefaultBinaryExpr
        • org.cloudgraph.query.expr.DefaultRelationalBinaryExpr
          • org.cloudgraph.hbase.graph.ExternalEdgeRecognizerRelationalBinaryExpr
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BinaryExpr, Expr, RelationalBinaryExpr, org.plasma.query.Term

    public class ExternalEdgeRecognizerRelationalBinaryExpr
extends DefaultRelationalBinaryExpr
implements RelationalBinaryExpr
    An RelationalBinaryExpr implementation which uses a specific evaluation context to locate or recognize a given sequence based column qualifier within the context of the expression.

    For external edges, we have only the row key fields to evaluate and the predicate tree may contain predicates with properties which target fields anywhere in the target graph including properties outside the row key. So for external edge evaluators always return true when a value is not found.

    Since:
    1.0.4
    Author:
    Scott Cinnamond

      • evaluate

        public boolean evaluate(EvaluationContext context)
        Returns a "truth" value for the expression using a specific evaluation context to locate or recognize a given row key field within the context of the expression.

        For external edges, we have only the row key fields to evaluate and the predicate tree may contain predicates with properties which target fields anywhere in the target graph including properties outside the row key. So for external edge evaluators always return true when a value is not found, but indicate the row evaluation was not complete so downstream actions can be taken.
